#TrackNigeria —A 43- year  old bus driver, named Kabiru Bello has committed suicide at a  mechanic workshop in Lagos with substances suspected to be Sniper, police said. The State police Command Spokesman,DSP
Bala Elkana said in a statement that “Shomolu Pedro Police Station received an
information that one Kabiru Bello ‘m’  43yrs old, of No 77 Owode Ibeshe,
Ikorodu Lagos  allegedly drank  a liquid substance suspected to be
sniper chemical in his Volkswagen commercial Bus with registration number AKD
724 XM, while at a mechanic workshop at Ladylack Bus stop, Shomolu.” He was then  rushed to Adesola clinic Shomolu where he
was  confirmed dead. Homicide detectives  who visited the scene  found one empty bottle of chemical substance
suspected to be sniper.It  has been
recovered, the police  said The corpse has been deposited in
mortuary for autopsy. ..As police recover two single barrel guns from fleeing  armed
robbery suspects Also the statement said Ilemba Hausa
Police Station received a distress call that one Wale Lawal was dispossessed of
his laptop by some armed robbers. A team of Policemen deployed to the
scene gave the hoodlums a hot chase and they abandoned their black Honda
vehicle with registration number Lagos KJA 705 BU. An on the spot search was carried
out on the vehicle.In the  process, two
locally made single barrel guns with twelve life cartridges, one laptop 
and one mobile phone were recovered inside  the vehicle. The vehicle was moved to the station for further investigation, which Elkana
said is ongoing.